description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Facilitator (AHP pre-reg students) – 12 months FTC (secondment considered). &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6, 1.0 WTE (37.5 hrs/pw)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic, enthusiastic and motivated current HCPC registered AHP to work as a Clinical Facilitator for AHP students. Your remit is to expand and support placement capacity with clear performance metrics. You will work in conjunction with our AHP Practice Educator for pre-registration students to contribute to and ensure the provision of high quality practice placements within the expansion programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve working with students from Occupational Therapy, Physiotherapy, Speech and Language Therapy, and Dietetics. Placements are delivered at Peterborough City Hospital, Hinchingbrooke Hospital and Stamford Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must be confident and enjoy teaching others, sharing knowledge and be a professional role model. They must demonstrate evidence of ongoing CPD and have recent experience as a practice educator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to foster good relationships with the practice educators and external stake holders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be a requirement for attendance at relevant departmental, wider trust and off-site meetings as appropriate, and a requirement to deputise for the AHP Practice Educator at times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rachel Redford: AHP Practice Educator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;r.redford@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01733 673669&lt;/p&gt;
